Message: Even though pleasure won't last forever, as long as Commandant is here, we'll surely have much more pleasure again!
It was so fun hanging around with Commandant, but I felt there weren't enough kinds of drinks. Next time, we'll handle the drinks for you. Speech input ended. Oh, Is it this button?
Commandant, after the event ends, please don't push yourself too hard and take rest days whenever you need to... Well then, I'll go to look for other members.
On behalf of the Engineering Force, we hope to see you again at the next event. I'm only speaking on behalf of the Engineering Force, okay?
It was getting noisier when people gathered around. Let's go somewhere quieter next time, just the two of us.
I'd have brought my harmonica if I'd known there would be so many events around. I'm looking forward to giving everyone my best performance next time.
With the sea waves softly rolling in and birds soaring in the sky, it couldn't be any better to create art with you.
We must hold an event like this one more time, Commandant! Let's meet up next week. I can't wait to see your event proposal! This is what Nanami wanted to tell you.
I've been told that I should wear something more appropriate for an event like this. What are your thoughts, Commandant? Or can you help me select my clothes?
It's good to have a place where you can soak your body in sea water. Thank you for bringing me here, Commandant.
Were you able to dig up this message, Commandant? This was pretty like how we dug you out of the sand. Perhaps we should just throw it into the sea next time.
A very entertaining event indeed. If that's possible, I'd love to have it in Kowloong as well. Would you help me out if that happens?
Did you enjoy the show, Commandant? It really feels good to forget everything and enjoy the sea from time to time, doesn't it?
When our squad was having a beach volleyball game, Lillian accidentally slammed the ball into Captain Palma's face. The anger in her eyes was...

SingleMessage: It's been another year already. With you alongside us, the Gray Ravens will keep on striving toward a new future.
Another year that we've spent together has passed. I hope I can leave an anniversary message to you in each of the following years, Commandant.
It's good to see the Gray Raven, even after moving on to another new logbook, is still whole with everyone sticking together.
It has been a year brimming with cherished memories, Commandant. Let's continue this journey together in the times that lie ahead.
I've just unlocked a trophy for spending a year with you, Commandant. Can't wait to earn even more trophies in the new year!
It was a truly hectic year, wasn't it? Don't push yourself too hard, y'know. Watch over your sleep time, quality, hideout...
No matter how many years have passed, there's only one thing I can do for you and them—destroy everything that gets in the way.
A year has passed, which means I've already observed you for a whole year... That said, time itself has no meaning to me.
The only thing that matters is not how long we've been together, but what we want to achieve together. Hope you can find it to sustain our relationship.
A year's plays have ended. I wonder what plays are in store for the new year. How about you, Commandant? Want some... surprise?

RewardName: Arrival Target / Fate Arrival Target Character
SingleMessage: This is specifically for you, so you gotta come over and say your thank you in person, got it?
To commemorate our anniversary, I've drawn a portrait of you. What do you say we take a look at it together in my art studio?
Even though I'm not here with you, I wish the wind of fortune will blow behind your sails, Commandant.
Congratulations on getting my anniversary message, Commandant! Collect six more and you'll be able to summon Nanami!
In return for your companionship over the past year, I shall accompany you through the new year. A reasonable exchange indeed.
I must say over the past year, you often pushed yourself too much. Please remember I'm here for you whenever things stress you out.

RewardName: Arrival Target / Fate Arrival Target Character
SingleMessage: Two questions: Any idea how many messes I cleaned up for you over the past year? How're you gonna repay me in the new year?
Commandant, let's celebrate the anniversary with some card games. You, me, and Buddy... Perfect.
A year has gone by, yet my spear will remain at your service, ready to wipe out any obstacles in your path, Commandant.
As time flies by, everything changes. Though I often find this pleasurable, something should just stay as is. Don't you think so, Commandant?
Wow, it's already been another year?! I was barely even aware of it! Let's make an anniversary cake together, Commandant!
I hope this will bring blessings upon you, Commandant. May you be safe and happy in the new year.
Bambinata from the past would want you to have this. Thank you for your caring and kindness, Commandant.
Another year passed. You know you're welcome to drop by anytime you want. I've just got a new guitar. I want you to listen to a song I created recently.

RewardName: Arrival Target / Fate Arrival Target Character
SingleMessage: I'm looking forward to continuing the pursuit of the goals left undone from last year with you, Commandant.
Into the new year we go! Let me know anytime you need backup. All the bills've been sent to Nikola's office, don't worry!
Commandant, can I put my wish note with yours in the same bottle? Yes, I want to drift in the same space and on the same sea with you.
I put my wish in the bottle... Yeah, mine. It's my own wish, but it's a wish about you... about us.
I didn't understand the meaning behind this, but now... Ahem. Alright, I reinforced our bottle with a stronger material. Now it can reach a place more far beyond your imagination.
I don't care about the reason, because I will find the answer that I want from you.
The endless journey is one of the few things we share together, but what kind of ending do you want?
Look, a ship is traveling in the bottle. Captain Rolmo, who seems free, is actually trapped in an invisible prison. Poor guy.
I like the bottle. I want to drift away in the sea like that and speak my mind to someone on the beach. Would you like to... Um... Forget it.
I put some grain seeds in the bottle, hoping it can help other people. Do you want to do this with me, Commandant?

RewardName: Arrival Target / Fate Arrival Target Character
SingleMessage: The bottle is full of my gratitude to you. Get it out of the sea if you're curious. But I guess it has probably sunk to the bottom of the sea.
Write my wish on this note, and put it inside a bottle to drift away? Um... Did you just release this bottle, Commandant? I got it, so it's mine now.
We should throw the bottles as far as we can! Commandant, give me yours! I'll throw them away together!
I put a sketch of Commandant and me in the bottle. It feels like we are traveling around the world together, doesn't it?
We are drifting in the river of time like it, but as long as we follow our hearts, we will eventually reach our destination. Don't you think so, Conductor?
A message that is not intended to reach the destination... A proposal of Commandant's style. I like it.
There is no ocean near the flying fortress. I once made a drift bottle like the books said, but I never had a chance to release it... Commandant? Shall I just put it in the ocean now?

RewardName: Arrival Target / Fate Arrival Target Character
SingleMessage: I put your name on the letter because I hope you're also involved in this journey.
I even included a chip with the backup data of the game we played! Don't you think it's super cool to share the world we built together with the next person?
Um, are you relying on the sea to fulfill your wish? Don't you see that the person capable of doing this right next to you...? Feel like I'm challenged.
Why put your secrets in a bottle and send it to a stranger? Throw it away! If you have anything to say, say it. And I'll do the same.
Hey, give me the button on your chest! Hurry! Don't get me wrong. I just want to check if quantum mechanics work...
When I was a kid, I used to write down things that made me upset and put them in a drift bottle, hoping they would go away. But now, I can put in happiness that I would like to share with others.
No matter how it ends, they will leave undying traces just like us. So just let it go with the flow.
See you, Mr. Bottle. Hope you can go where you want to go just like me!
Let's run away with our wishes like the bottle.
This bottle is going to the sea. And this one... is for Bambinata to keep, because Bambinata doesn't want to forget this memory.
...Great! Now our bottles can travel together! Don't you dare to separate! No! Never!
Searching and protecting my own people is top priority, so I leave your contact info on the communication medium in the bottle.
Do you want to put the note with your wish into the bottle? Let me write it for you... Do you like this calligraphy style?

RewardName: Arrival Target / Fate Arrival Target Character
SingleMessage: It's said that these bottles would drift to a deep pit with all the lost treasure in the world, so I put a tracker in each of them.
Put something meaningful to you in it? ... Commandant, what would you put? Just for reference.
